buttons.snippet: Mastic has a slightly resinous, pine-like flavour and can be chewed just like chewing gum. Mastic is also used in traditional Tsoureki, a Greek bread made at Easter.

buttons.subtitle: Origin Of Mastic
buttons.title: Mastic (plant resin) - Wikipedia
buttons.snippet: Mastic (Greek: Μαστίχα) is a resin obtained from the mastic tree (Pistacia lentiscus). It is also known as tears of Chios, being traditionally produced on the island Chios, and, like other natural resins, is produced in "tears" or droplets.
